        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 5:08PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Greenfield, or near Jonesboro, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hergett, Apt, Delfore, Lake City, Tulot, Valley View, Hatchie Coon,
Gum Point, Farrville, Lester, Craighead Forest Park, Maple Grove,
Lepanto, Jonesboro, Promised Land, Caraway, Cary, Harrisburg, Judd
Hill, and Lache Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
eastern Arkansas.</instruction>
